{
  "texts": [
    "However, there are several difficulties with this approach at the transfer stage.",
    "First, single-modal fashion designs require high-resolution textural details, and low-resolution fashion items cannot clearly illustrate the effects of style transfer.",
    "Second, a fashion design system needs to capture the boundaries of a texture filling accurately.",
    "In addition, some parts of fashion items do not need texture padding, such as buttons, zippers, etc.",
    "With the help of the controllable generation features of a GAN, many researchers have generated refined and user-controllable fashion items."
  ]
}